main event: A bright, rapidly moving object was observed by several people at the Kokomo Airport control tower on May 7, 1964 around 11:30 PM.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, rapidly moving object that appeared to move in an erratic manner and seemed to be at a high altitude.
The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes.
No sound was heard from the object.
The object disappeared from view in the northeasterly direction.
The report includes a Project 10073 Record Card with details about the sighting, including the date, location, type of observation, source, length of observation, number of objects, and conclusions.
witnesses: Several persons on duty at the Kokomo Airport control tower
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs
